<subSubSection pageNumber="916" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="916">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="916">Note:</emphasis>
The Clifford material was proposed as the conserved type by Jeffrey (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="916">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 595. 1992), subsequently recommended by both the Committee for Spermatophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="916">Taxon</emphasis>
43: 276. 1994) and the General Committee (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="916">Taxon</emphasis>
43: 281. 1994). Olsen (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="916">Brittonia</emphasis>
38: 364. 1986) was credited as being the typifier by Jeffrey in his proposal. However, Wijnands had already made the same choice.
</paragraph>
